<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="201" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/3–949: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-09">March 9,
                                1949</date>.<lb/>[Received March 9—10:56 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>548. Vernacular press March 9 reports Legislative Yuan yesterday passed
                            resolution requesting Premier, heads of important Ministries <pb facs="0178" n="168" xml:id="pg_168"/> and Commissions and Ministers
                            without Portfolio to return Nanking and manage political affairs from
                            here during period of peace talks. Sent Department 548; repeated Embassy
                            Canton unnumbered.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>